Circle|Circle of Eighteen	A cabal of powerful sorcerers who led the immense Rebel armies against the Lady's Empire. Drawn heavily from the eastern border regions of the Empire, the Circle organized and directed massive military campaigns against Imperial forces across the northern continent. Among its most notable members were the commanders Raker, Whisper, and Harden; Whisper and Harden were cousins, while Raker and Harden were brothers-in-law, suggesting a partly familial alliance. Known to use brutal tactics, the Circle also devoted considerable resources to searching for the prophesied reincarnation of the White Rose.
Pastel Wars	A series of major conflicts fought near the Second Cataract of the great river of the southern continent, approximately two hundred years before the events of The Black Company. The warring parties were Cho'n Delor on the river's east bank—ruled by a brutal tyrant called the Paingod, with the Black Company as his enforcers—and the Triplet Cities on the west bank. The Triplet Cities ultimately prevailed, but the cost was so catastrophic that both sides were reduced to ruins, the land so scarred and haunted that even animals shunned it for centuries afterward. At the time of the wars, the Black Company was in its second century, more than six thousand strong, and all its men were black. The conflict's turbulence cost the Company four successive Annalists—Lees, Agrip, Holm, and Straw—and the early Annals were lost during the fighting. The wars were also noted for a distinctive style of battlefield sorcery: soft ribbons of pastel light in pinks, greens, yellows, and blues that undulated like seaweed and drifted downward to engulf their targets.
TelleKurre|KurreTelle	The name of both a language and its native people, once the primary tongue and ruling ethnic group of the Domination. Under the Dominator's reign, the TelleKurre were elevated far above all other groups in his empire. The language was rendered extinct following the White Rose Rebellion, when TelleKurre cities were burned and their populations scattered. A regional vulgate called UchiTelle was also spoken. The spelling of TelleKurre names was notoriously free-form, with various letter combinations representing identical sounds.
Ten Who Were Taken|Taken	Ten notorious sorcerers of very high magnitude enslaved by the Dominator approximately five centuries before the events of The Black Company. Consisting of seven men and three women, they served as the Dominator's most powerful generals in establishing the cruel era known as the Domination. After the White Rose's Rebellion, they were imprisoned alongside the Dominator and the Lady in the Barrowland for 370 years. By the opening of The Black Company, they had been in the service of the Lady's Empire for nearly 37 years. Their names—Soulcatcher, the Limper, the Howler, Shapeshifter, Stormbringer, the Hanged Man, Bonegnasher, Nightcrawler, Moonbiter, and the Faceless Man—were derived from their sorcerous specialties or appearance, and are translations from TelleKurre, the language of the Domination. Each was powerful enough to overwhelm most other sorcerers and, with preparation, could defeat hundreds of soldiers.
